14:07.720 --> 14:09.882
<i>Meet the crew, hoo-hoo!</i>

14:09.960 --> 14:14.045
I'm local San Diego legend Champ Kind,
and I believe in two things.

14:14.120 --> 14:15.087
Good chicken,

14:15.160 --> 14:19.290
and that the census is a way for
the U.N. to make your children gay.

14:19.360 --> 14:21.408
So come on by and grab a wing.

14:21.480 --> 14:24.563
<i>'Cause when you do,
you'll say, "Whammy!"</i>

14:24.800 --> 14:26.643
<i>No Catholics or Jews admitted.</i>

14:26.760 --> 14:27.966
All right, there you go.

14:28.040 --> 14:30.691
One Whammy Special
with Whammy slaw.

14:31.040 --> 14:33.930
There's a used Band-Aid
in my coleslaw.

14:34.000 --> 14:36.002
My gosh, let me take care of that.

14:36.080 --> 14:39.482
Get out of here before I smash
your head in, you Commie bastard!

14:39.560 --> 14:42.166
If you're from the census,
you take me off your list!

14:43.400 --> 14:46.051
You never did have much
of a bedside manner, Champ.

14:46.120 --> 14:48.088
Ron? Ron Burgundy?

14:48.160 --> 14:50.367
- Get over here!
- How are you, friend?

14:50.440 --> 14:52.761
God, I have longed for you.

14:52.920 --> 14:54.285
It's good to see you, too.

14:54.360 --> 14:55.850
Oh, this feels like home.

14:56.520 --> 14:57.601
Are you all right?

14:57.680 --> 14:59.728
Yeah, I'm fine. Better now.

14:59.840 --> 15:02.571
Okay, let's break the huddle here, huh?

15:03.480 --> 15:05.005
- Okay. All right.
- All right.

15:05.080 --> 15:06.889
You get back here!

15:06.960 --> 15:08.121
Don't be weird!

15:08.640 --> 15:10.927
<font color="#808080">CHAMP:</font> So, anyway,
Harken sat me down, he said,

15:11.000 --> 15:14.004
"Champ, you're a dangerous alcoholic,
a racist,"

15:14.080 --> 15:16.686
"and I don't think
you know a lick about sports."

15:16.760 --> 15:20.446
And I said, "Ed, you dirty Polack,
it's 10:00 in the morning."

15:20.520 --> 15:21.806
"Let's go have some drinks"

15:21.880 --> 15:24.963
"and go to a baseball game where
the Mexicans hit some touchdowns."

15:25.040 --> 15:26.087
Then he fires me!

15:26.160 --> 15:30.449
Fortunately, on the way out the door,
I fake a work injury.

15:30.520 --> 15:32.443
With the settlement, I bought this place.

15:32.520 --> 15:34.727
Well, I'm glad to see
you landed on your feet, Champ.

15:35.680 --> 15:37.444
Listen, can I ask you a question?

15:37.640 --> 15:39.085
Sure. Anything.

15:39.480 --> 15:41.005
Is... Is this chicken?

15:41.080 --> 15:42.923
Oh, hell, no.

15:43.240 --> 15:46.562
It's really impossible to turn a profit
if you serve real chicken.

15:46.840 --> 15:48.808
Yeah. We use mainly bats.

15:48.880 --> 15:49.881
- What?
- Yeah.

15:49.960 --> 15:52.042
But the good quality kind.

15:52.240 --> 15:54.163
That's the most horrible thing
I've ever heard.

15:54.240 --> 15:55.207
Yeah?

15:55.280 --> 15:57.248
You got to do what you got to do, right?

15:57.320 --> 15:59.448
So what you got to do
is serve fried bats?

15:59.560 --> 16:02.211
Yep. Do you know what they call bats?

16:02.440 --> 16:04.681
- Bats.
- "Chicken of the Cave."

16:04.760 --> 16:06.728
No one calls them Chicken of the Cave.

16:06.800 --> 16:08.211
Who's "they," by the way?

16:08.600 --> 16:12.685
There's a guy I met named Paco,
sells bikers speed at the pier.

16:12.760 --> 16:15.411
So that guy calls them
Chicken of the Cave.

16:15.480 --> 16:16.481
Yeah.

16:16.560 --> 16:17.846
That's not "they."

16:17.920 --> 16:20.207
Why don't you have a bite
and stop judging it?

16:20.280 --> 16:22.009
I'm not going to bite into a fried bat.

16:22.080 --> 16:23.127
It's delicious.

16:23.200 --> 16:24.964
It's all tendon. Look at it.

16:25.120 --> 16:26.963
<font color="#D900D9">(PEOPLE SCREAMING)</font>

16:27.880 --> 16:29.120
Was that a bat?

16:29.440 --> 16:31.283
Chicken of the Cave.

16:31.520 --> 16:33.090
What brings you here, Ron?

16:33.240 --> 16:36.767
My friend, we've got a job.
In New York City.

16:36.840 --> 16:38.444
Whammy! I'm in!

16:38.640 --> 16:39.971
You've got yourself a sportscaster.

16:40.040 --> 16:41.041
Oh, great.

16:41.120 --> 16:42.281
Denny!

16:43.800 --> 16:45.040
Lock up!

16:45.440 --> 16:47.010
Any idea where Brian Fantana is?

16:47.080 --> 16:48.570
You haven't heard?

16:48.640 --> 16:50.324
Fantana hit the big time.

16:50.760 --> 16:52.762
Aw, baby.

16:53.720 --> 16:57.202
Yeah, that's it, play for me.
Just play around.

16:57.440 --> 17:00.091
Roll around and lift those legs up. Mmm!

17:00.920 --> 17:03.127
You are a hairy little thing, aren't you?

17:03.280 --> 17:04.361
<font color="#D900D9">(BRIAN GROWLS)</font>
<font color="#D900D9">(CAMERA CLICKING)</font>

17:04.440 --> 17:07.489
Yeah. Oh, I like what's happening!

17:07.800 --> 17:10.371
Oh, that's it. Yeah. Yeah.

17:10.560 --> 17:13.530
Oh, you little fuzzball, that's... Oh!

17:15.599 --> 17:17.409
I got it.
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL APPLAUDING)</font>

17:17.720 --> 17:20.200
It's not getting any better than that.

17:20.800 --> 17:22.290
- That's brilliant!
- Yeah, yeah.

17:22.359 --> 17:24.681
Hey, Brian,
you have any time for the little people?

17:28.000 --> 17:30.401
Well, I'll be a son of a bitch.

17:30.920 --> 17:32.570
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL LAUGHING)</font>

17:33.600 --> 17:36.251
- Hey, Brian.
- Champ! How you doing?

17:36.320 --> 17:37.401
Hey!

17:37.480 --> 17:38.891
- Wow. This is a...
- Cool it!

17:38.960 --> 17:40.485
Oh, I can't believe...

17:40.560 --> 17:42.164
Oh, wow.
It's great to see you!

17:42.240 --> 17:44.766
Welcome. Welcome to my doj'.

17:45.120 --> 17:46.724
This place is spectacular!

17:46.800 --> 17:48.040
- It's amazing.
- A bit chaotic today.

17:48.120 --> 17:50.088
We got the Cat <i>Fancy</i> cover coming out.

17:50.160 --> 17:51.605
- You know how that can be.
- Ooh.

17:51.680 --> 17:53.364
I've been living in a tent
for the last two years.

17:53.440 --> 17:54.930
Oh, yeah, this is not that.

17:55.000 --> 17:56.490
We got a sauna in the kitchen.

17:56.560 --> 17:59.928
A lot of people think that's weird,
but I keep wine in it.

18:00.000 --> 18:02.571
I'm not a wine guy,
but I know you got to keep it hot.

18:02.640 --> 18:04.563
Oh, and check this out.

18:04.640 --> 18:06.404
This... This was fun.

18:06.560 --> 18:08.324
We shot this over two weeks in Prague.

18:08.440 --> 18:09.601
<font color="#808080">RON:</font> Wow.

18:09.720 --> 18:11.848
You know what they call cats?

18:11.920 --> 18:14.321
- Chicken of the rail yard.
- No.

18:14.520 --> 18:16.284
- What?
- Don't indulge him.

18:16.400 --> 18:17.970
- Yeah.
<font color="#808080">CHAMP:</font> - There's a lot of meat.

18:18.040 --> 18:19.485
But I love it. <font color="#D900D9">(CHUCKLES)</font>

18:19.560 --> 18:22.484
And what's so great about it
is it's so damn true.

18:22.560 --> 18:23.607
I hate Mondays!

18:23.880 --> 18:25.769
I'm not a Monday guy.

18:25.840 --> 18:27.604
Ron hates Mondays.

18:27.680 --> 18:29.682
Hell, I'm not crazy about them, either.

18:29.760 --> 18:32.001
I also don't like Tuesdays,
Wednesdays or Thursdays.

18:32.080 --> 18:33.570
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL LAUGHING)</font>

18:33.680 --> 18:35.489
So why are you guys here, anyway?

18:35.560 --> 18:39.485
Well, Brian, we're getting
the news team back together again.

18:39.560 --> 18:40.527
Really?

18:40.640 --> 18:42.847
And, of course,
we want to know if you'll join us.

18:42.920 --> 18:44.365
Jeez, I don't know.

18:44.440 --> 18:46.966
I kind of got the world by the tail here.

18:47.040 --> 18:48.644
I don't know if I can.

18:48.720 --> 18:49.801
Christ, I get it.

18:49.880 --> 18:51.882
I mean, you're the Quincy Jones
of cat photographers.

18:51.960 --> 18:53.291
Why would you leave all this?

18:53.440 --> 18:54.965
<font color="#808080">RON:</font> Hey, Brian,
I don't know if you heard,

18:55.040 --> 18:57.691
but New York has all-nude strip clubs.

19:00.440 --> 19:02.488
The question still remains...

19:02.880 --> 19:04.450
Where's Brick Tamland?

19:04.560 --> 19:05.686
Oh.

19:05.760 --> 19:07.364
You guys didn't hear?

19:07.440 --> 19:08.885
No, what happened?

19:09.000 --> 19:10.047
Brick's...

19:11.640 --> 19:13.005
Dead.

19:21.440 --> 19:22.805
<font color="#808080">BRIAN:</font> Brick was lost at sea

19:22.880 --> 19:24.211
- about a year ago.
<font color="#808080">RON:</font> - Oh.

19:24.520 --> 19:27.046
Thought he saw a bird
and he swam out to pet it.

19:27.120 --> 19:28.281
He never came back.

19:28.680 --> 19:31.081
<font color="#D900D9">(PEOPLE SOBBING)</font>
We all loved Brick,

19:31.160 --> 19:33.686
even though he never had
a phone number,

19:33.760 --> 19:37.082
or address or Social Security number.

19:37.160 --> 19:40.801
In six years of working at the station,
he never cashed a paycheck.

19:40.880 --> 19:42.006
That sweet Brick.

19:42.080 --> 19:43.480
<font color="#808080">ED:</font> He was a sensitive man, though.

19:43.520 --> 19:48.651
He told me he wanted to donate
his organs to science before he died,

19:48.840 --> 19:51.320
so he could see where they ended up.

19:51.880 --> 19:55.646
He'll long be remembered
and he'll be sorely missed.

19:56.960 --> 19:58.200
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

20:00.560 --> 20:02.369
Thank you, Reverend.

20:02.840 --> 20:04.888
- Oh.
- Oh, come on!

20:05.000 --> 20:07.162
<font color="#808080">BRICK:</font> Brick was a great man.
<font color="#D900D9">(SCOFFS)</font> Really?

20:07.240 --> 20:08.844
And I will miss him so much.

20:08.920 --> 20:11.526
And I will not rest until I find his killer.

20:11.600 --> 20:12.965
- What?
- His killer?

20:13.040 --> 20:16.123
It is hard for me
to believe that he is gone. <font color="#D900D9">(SOBS)</font>

20:16.520 --> 20:18.249
He's not gone.

20:18.680 --> 20:21.570
<font color="#D900D9">(SOBBING)</font> I feel that
I just saw him yesterday.

20:21.640 --> 20:23.608
You were probably
talking to yourself in a mirror.

20:23.680 --> 20:26.843
<font color="#808080">BRICK:</font> When I got the news...
<font color="#D900D9">(CONTINUES SOBBING)</font>

20:27.000 --> 20:30.163
I didn't even know
how to make sense out of it!

20:30.280 --> 20:31.486
None of us understand!

20:31.720 --> 20:33.609
<font color="#D900D9">(SHOUTS)</font> Why? Why?

20:34.040 --> 20:36.008
Why did you take him from us?

20:36.080 --> 20:38.560
You're clearly standing in front of us,
Brick.

20:38.640 --> 20:40.005
God damn you!

20:40.160 --> 20:42.083
- Brick!
- Brick is dead!

20:42.160 --> 20:43.969
<font color="#808080">RON:</font> - No, Brick's alive.
- Brick is dead!

20:44.040 --> 20:45.371
- Look at him!
- He's not dead.

20:45.440 --> 20:46.680
He's not dead, Brick. You're not dead.

20:46.760 --> 20:48.205
- You're Brick!
- Brick, it's you!

20:48.280 --> 20:49.611
He's dead!

20:49.680 --> 20:50.681
No!

20:50.760 --> 20:53.001
You are Brick! Touch yourself.

20:53.080 --> 20:55.447
- I am Brick?
<font color="#808080">ALL:</font> - Yes!

20:55.720 --> 20:57.768
- I'm alive?
<font color="#808080">ALL:</font> - Yes!

20:57.880 --> 20:59.370
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING JOYFULLY)</font>
<font color="#808080">ED:</font> Of course.

20:59.440 --> 21:00.851
Of course you are.

21:00.920 --> 21:02.160
<font color="#808080">ED:</font> Oh, for heaven's sake.

21:02.280 --> 21:04.931
You kind of want to slug him.
You want to slug him.

21:05.000 --> 21:06.843
<font color="#D900D9">(ANCHORMEN LAUGHING)</font>

21:08.200 --> 21:11.886
<font color="#808080">RON:</font> Do you remember
our Easter trip to San Francisco?

21:11.960 --> 21:14.964
We got so drunk,
we put Brick in a refrigerator box

21:15.040 --> 21:17.805
and threw him off
the Golden Gate Bridge.

21:18.720 --> 21:19.846
I broke my back!

21:19.960 --> 21:21.041
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL LAUGHING)</font>

21:21.440 --> 21:23.204
What about the time
that you dared Champ

21:23.280 --> 21:25.567
to drink that beer stein full of Woolite?

21:25.640 --> 21:28.041
He drained it faster than you could say,
"No, don't do it."

21:28.120 --> 21:30.122
"That's the equivalent of
drinking poison."

21:30.200 --> 21:32.043
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL LAUGHING)</font>

21:32.120 --> 21:35.283
Oh, Lord, I was in a six-month coma.

21:35.480 --> 21:37.608
And they say from
the neurological damage,

21:37.680 --> 21:40.923
there's no way I live past 55!
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING)</font>

21:42.800 --> 21:44.882
You got three years left, my friend.

21:44.960 --> 21:46.803
You're gonna die!

21:48.920 --> 21:50.251
Hey, hey, remember?

21:50.320 --> 21:54.484
I was by myself and I had that dream
about the orange tree.

21:54.560 --> 21:57.564
But instead of oranges,
it had babies on it.

21:58.160 --> 22:00.731
It was a baby tree! <font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING)</font>

22:01.120 --> 22:03.646
Brick, how could we remember?
It's your dream.

22:03.720 --> 22:07.167
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING)</font> I don't know.
It's all the same thing.

22:09.120 --> 22:12.010
It's an interesting dream,
but we're telling stories

22:12.080 --> 22:14.162
involving the entire news team
from the past.

22:14.240 --> 22:15.765
<font color="#D900D9">(BRICK LAUGHS)</font>

22:15.840 --> 22:21.529
Or how about the time when I was born
and I came out of the vagina?

22:21.600 --> 22:22.681
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING)</font>

22:22.800 --> 22:28.045
I was screaming,
"Here I come! Oh! Here I come, Mom!"

22:29.480 --> 22:32.450
First off, Brick, I highly doubt
you remember your own birth.

22:32.520 --> 22:35.364
And, once again, we weren't there.

22:35.440 --> 22:36.930
<font color="#D900D9">(CONTINUES LAUGHING)</font>

22:38.840 --> 22:40.410
Ron, I can't...

22:40.520 --> 22:42.887
I can't stop laughing, Ron!

22:43.200 --> 22:44.884
Put a pencil in his mouth.

22:45.080 --> 22:46.320
<font color="#808080">RON:</font> It's okay.

22:46.920 --> 22:48.160
<font color="#808080">CHAMP:</font> There you go.

22:48.240 --> 22:49.969
I'm okay now.

22:50.040 --> 22:53.328
Man, this just feels right!
The news team is back!

22:53.680 --> 22:57.765
Ron, Brian, Brick, me, even Baxter!

22:57.880 --> 22:59.803
<font color="#D900D9">(BARKING)</font>
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING)</font>

22:59.880 --> 23:02.087
That old man is so little and hairy!

23:03.200 --> 23:04.486
Hey, Ron, who's driving?

23:04.560 --> 23:06.562
Oh, it's okay, it's on cruise control.

23:08.880 --> 23:11.008
Who wants some chimichangas, huh?

23:11.320 --> 23:14.608
Best thing I ever did was install
this deep fryer in the 'bago.

23:14.880 --> 23:17.451
Ron, why do you have
this bag of bowling balls

23:17.520 --> 23:19.727
and this terrarium filled with scorpions?

23:19.800 --> 23:22.770
- Oh, it's a long, crazy story!
<font color="#808080">BRIAN:</font> - Hey, Ron.

23:22.880 --> 23:25.360
Cruise control just regulates speed,
it doesn't steer.

23:26.520 --> 23:27.965
- Come again?
<font color="#808080">CHAMP:</font> - Oh!

23:28.200 --> 23:29.440
<font color="#D900D9">(HONKING)</font>

23:29.520 --> 23:31.045
<font color="#D900D9">(TIRES SCREECHING)</font>

23:33.960 --> 23:36.008
<font color="#D900D9">(SOFT MUSIC PLAYING)</font>

23:39.760 --> 23:41.364
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMING)</font>

23:49.120 --> 23:50.884
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMS)</font>

23:54.600 --> 23:55.886
<font color="#D900D9">(SNARLING)</font>

23:56.000 --> 23:57.286
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMING)</font>

24:03.240 --> 24:05.607
<font color="#D900D9">(RON WHIMPERING)</font>

24:07.680 --> 24:09.569
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMING)</font>

24:12.240 --> 24:13.730
<font color="#D900D9">(GROANING)</font>

24:27.200 --> 24:29.965
<font color="#808080">RON:</font> Well, that is gonna
make one hell of a story.

24:30.040 --> 24:31.690
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL LAUGHING)</font>

24:37.520 --> 24:40.444
The Big Apple. Ron Burgundy is back.

24:40.520 --> 24:42.522
<font color="#808080">CHAMP:</font> Why do they call it
the Big Apple, Ron?

24:42.600 --> 24:45.604
<font color="#808080">RON:</font> Because New York has
an apple tree on every street.

24:48.360 --> 24:51.443
Here we are. Welcome to GNN.

24:54.400 --> 24:57.051
I don't know, Ron.
You sure about this place?

24:57.120 --> 24:59.441
Guys, I know it's a bit of a mess,
but trust me,

24:59.560 --> 25:02.450
everything will be ready
for the launch tomorrow.

25:02.560 --> 25:06.485
And we've culled the whole country
for the best newsmen.

25:06.560 --> 25:08.210
There's Curtis Knightfish from Houston.

25:08.280 --> 25:09.566
Oh, Curtis Knightfish.

25:09.640 --> 25:11.404
They don't get any better than that.

25:11.480 --> 25:14.563
<font color="#808080">FREDDIE:</font> And there's Diane
Yahwea from Carson City.

25:14.640 --> 25:17.166
Diane Yahwea.
You know what they call her, right?

25:17.240 --> 25:18.924
"All the Way Yahwea."

25:19.000 --> 25:20.365
She's my aunt.

25:20.440 --> 25:22.568
And the best in the biz.

25:22.640 --> 25:25.166
Jack Lime, out of Chicago.

25:25.320 --> 25:29.325
Rumor is Allenby
is giving him one mil a year.

25:29.440 --> 25:31.602
That's crazy.
Who's worth that kind of money?

25:33.320 --> 25:36.563
<font color="#808080">RON:</font> Oh, my God!
He's absolutely magnificent!

25:37.040 --> 25:39.646
I bet his poop smells like sandalwood.

25:39.720 --> 25:41.324
Can I help you, guy?

25:41.480 --> 25:42.925
<font color="#D900D9">(STAMMERS)</font> What was that?

25:43.000 --> 25:44.411
I said, "Can I help you, guy?"

25:44.520 --> 25:46.807
Uh... <font color="#D900D9">(CLEARS THROAT)</font>
What do you mean?

25:46.880 --> 25:49.281
Well, you're staring at me, hotshot.

25:49.400 --> 25:51.164
Do you want my autograph?

25:51.240 --> 25:52.924
<font color="#D900D9">(BOTH LAUGHING)</font>

25:53.200 --> 25:57.046
No, he was just explaining
who you were and I was looking at you.

25:57.120 --> 26:00.329
And then he said something
and I was still looking at you.

26:00.440 --> 26:02.761
<font color="#D900D9">(MUMBLES MOCKINGLY)</font>

26:03.160 --> 26:04.685
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL LAUGHING)</font>

26:06.760 --> 26:09.047
<font color="#D900D9">(IN HIGH-PITCHED VOICE)</font>
Jack Lime is a great man!

26:09.120 --> 26:10.610
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHING)</font>

26:11.160 --> 26:12.400
Is that what I sound like when I talk?

26:12.480 --> 26:14.164
<font color="#D900D9">(MUMBLES MOCKINGLY)</font>

26:14.240 --> 26:15.844
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL LAUGHING)</font>

26:16.600 --> 26:17.840
Is there a problem?

26:17.920 --> 26:19.888
No, no, no,
no, no, no, no. No problem.

26:19.960 --> 26:22.281
Well, you're making a face
like you got a problem.

26:22.360 --> 26:24.283
Um, I'm sorry that I'm making that face.

26:24.360 --> 26:27.523
I don't mean to make a face
that seems like I have a problem.

26:27.600 --> 26:28.931
I don't like that face!

26:29.000 --> 26:30.729
You need to change it,
and change it quick.

26:30.800 --> 26:32.131
